from what i can see dolfie dreams are resin cast as well. They warn you of the usage of acetone. Which is an good indicator these are resin cast.

But basically, you know my struggles with reading right. Well I've actually discovered a while ago, that factually have an EASIER time reading things when they're WRITTEN text, and not digital font text. I thought about that listening to that album with my new $5 glasses ear thingies, and my first guess is that, my mind ends up filling many gaps, which results in me not being PASSIVE while consuming the material.

So it's just been something I thought about today (and MAYBE that experience was just a fluke and won't hold up if I test it more!). Whatever one may think of it, it's at least an interesting perspective, and it helps me understand his aesthetic ideals more, and probably why I like his stuff so much.

ooh so many things so far out of the first one, for starts it's just so interesting to me, to have an american socialist's (who can also speak russian) perspective who was literally in the same room, and in regular correspondence with all of these legendary revolutionary figures, but moreover it's made me a looot more sympathetic to trotsky, and to a lesser degree lenin. before, i always had the idea that he was a ruthless power hungry ideologue (i literally bought into stalins narrative), and while he may still be an ideologue, he seemed to have a decent moral compass and genuine care for the state of the proletariat rather than just political power. it also struck me as morbidly ironic that the same people who collaborated with stalin against trotsky would suffer a much worse fate than if they would've just rallied behind trotsky in the first place.
>>10607210

If your pre-amp has an out, it may have a "direct monitor" feature which would allow you to hear. Otherwise I think you would need to go into your OS sound settings and "Listen to this device" to make the sound come out of your speakers, or headphones.
